 Remarks:
 These VIRGINIA Class exhibits reflect Block V incorporating changes for AS on all SSNs and VPM beginning with SSN 803.

 The program is currently planning the fifth MYP (Block VI) contract for FY 2025 - FY 2029 procurements.

 FY 2027 funds two VIRGINIA Class Submarine (VCS) with Virginia Payload Module (VPM), Advance Procurement (AP) for future SSNs, $40 million of Submarine Industrial Base (SIB) investment for construction
 spares to help de-risk schedules, as well as $1,728 million for Nuclear Shipbuilder Productivity Enhancements (Advance Procurement funded in Plans - see exhibit P-10).

 The Electronics profile fluctuation (FY 2019 - FY 2023) reflects improved alignment of non-recurring engineering support to physically and electronically integrate the pre-planned NPES TI-24 Tech Insertion
 configuration and various phased Undersea Dominance Payloads. The FY 2026 Electronics increase above inflation is for the addition of two Low-Cost Conformal Arrays (LCCA), one per hull. LCCA has been
 added to the VIRGINIA Class Submarine Block VI technical baseline (FY 2025 - FY 2029). The Electronics increase from FY 2026 to FY 2027 above normal inflation is driven by vendor material increases.

 FY 2027 includes Completion of Prior Year Shipbuilding Programs (cost-to-complete) for the Block IV FY 2018 SSNs 800 and 801 ($44.2 million), and FY 2019 SSNs 802 and 803 ($561.1 million) to finance the
 Government responsible portion of the shipbuilding construction contract overrun.

 FY 2025 Plans includes $2,213 million for Nuclear Shipbuilder Productivity Enhancements and $180 million for SIB investment.

 The FY2026 Total Ship estimate does not show $4,600,000 thousand and quantity of one funded in FY 2026 mandatory funding. Total ship estimate for FY 2026 is $9,989,109 thousand.




