 Remarks:
 CVN 79

 Increase of $214M from the FY 2026 budget submission. The increase within Basic Construction ($187.6M) and Change Orders ($19.3M) from the FY 2026 budget submission supports Advanced Arresting
 Gear (AAG) Water Twister MOD II testing, associated delay and disruption, time related services, continued Advanced Weapons Elevator (AWE) work, wage and overtime increases, surge in manning to support
 sea trials and preliminary acceptance and additional outside engineering and vendor support to provide a more complete ship at delivery. Realignments within Electronics ($3.582), Propulsion equipment
 $7.000M, HM&E $.317M, Other Costs $.745M and Ordnance $2.601M due to fact of life changes and actual execution to support the delivery of a fully capable ship in March 2027.

 CVN 80

 Basic Construction: Increase of $191.156M from the FY 2026 budget submission to support economic price adjustments, government production engineering and waterfront construction support and revised
 requirements for nuclear shipyard firefighting enhancements.

 Ordnance: Increase of $11.200M from the FY 2026 budget submission due to proper pricing of Enterprise Air Surveillance Radar (EASR).

 Other Costs: Increase of $8.100M from the FY 2026 budget submission due to proper pricing of Material and Handling Equipment (MHE).




