 Description:
 This Operational Safety and Improvement Program (OSIP) funds modifications to the T-45 training system to address the safety-of-flight risk known as engine surge and engine stall. T-45 has a propensity for
 engine surge that is a critical safety concern for a single engine training aircraft with over 900 surge events documented, including over 70 surges requiring engine shutdown and restart emergency action. All
 elements of the T-45 training system (wings, fuselage, engine, etc.) contribute to the incidences of engine surge and engine stall. The F405 engine continues to experience surge stall events, and the funding is
 for the recurring and non-recurring activities set forth in this OSIP. Kits include modifications to air vehicle (Inlet), engine and fuel control system.

 DEVELOPMENT STATUS/MAJOR DEVELOPMENT MILESTONES: Installations for Inlet modifications are in process. Non-Recurring Engineering efforts to modify the F405-RR-401 engine and fuel system
 continue with kit procurement.




