 F-35B depot aircraft installation costs will increase FY2027 due to an increase in the number of inductions and the number of modifications authorized to be installed during each induction. F-35B SLLP
 modifications are projected to complete in 2047. Delays in funding will put that completion date at risk.

 The FY 2027 request for F-35B Joint Strike Fighter (JSF) includes $428,881 thousand of discretionary and $81,000 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $509,881 thousand. The discretionary
 funds provide for Correction of Deficiency, Block 4, APG-85 Radar, Propulsion, and Reliability & Maintainability modification and retrofit products. The mandatory funds provide for Block 4 modification and retrofit
 products. Install costs for ECP kits procured with mandatory (reconciliation) funding will still remain as baseline requirements in FY28-To Complete.

 DEVELOPMENT STATUS/MAJOR DEVELOPMENT MILESTONES:
 The program continues to work on top fleet issues related to the structural deficiencies. Efforts continue NRE, kit procurements and installs that remove life restrictions on major structural components on the
 F-35B fleet.




