 F-35C depot aircraft installation costs will increase FY2027 due to an increase in the number of inductions and the number of modifications authorized to be installed during each induction. F-35C SLLP
 modifications are projected to complete in 2047. Delays in funding will put that completion date at risk.

 The FY 2027 request for F-35C Joint Strike Fighter (JSF) includes $135,612 thousand of discretionary and $81,000 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $216,612 thousand. The discretionary
 funds provide for Correction of Deficiency, Block 4, APG-85 Radar, Propulsion, and Reliability & Maintainability modification and retrofit products. The mandatory funds provide for Correction of Deficiency and
 Block 4 modification and retrofit products. Install costs for ECP kits procured with mandatory (reconciliation) funding will still remain as baseline requirements in FY28-To Complete.

 DEVELOPMENT STATUS/MAJOR DEVELOPMENT MILESTONES:
 The Program will induct its first aircraft for the CV Upper Wing Skin set of 29 SLLP modifications.




