 Description:
 This OSIP funds critical safety, obsolescence, avionics changes, air vehicle structure changes, and mission system modifications. OSIP 004-22 funds the modification and integration of the Detect And Avoid
 System (DAAS), Airborne Network Extension (ANE) /Sky Tower II, and Electronic Warfare (EW)) / Cloud Surfer II, PLEO mission systems, GFE and NRE in support of Inc II capabilities. Air vehicle modifications
 will continue as required and consists of Radar Altimeter, Radar Altimeter Antenna, cables and assemblies for Auto Takeoff Capability and Landing Capability, Radar Altimeter, GPS Dual Band Anti Jam Antenna,
 cables and assemblies for GPS Anti-Jam Antenna system.

 Additionally, the MALE (MQ-9A) system will continue to evolve as future capabilities are identified and incorporated to address reliability, maintainability, and safety issues as they arise. Funding will be used to
 support Class 1 Engineering Change Proposals (ECP's) which address Diminishing Manufacturing Sources (DMS) and may include Non-Recurring Engineering (NRE).

 [Detect And Avoid System (DAAS) (AV) A-Kit] Provides a sensor package capable of due-regard flight operations in the USINDOPACOM Area of Responsibility (AOR) and CONUS NAS, meeting Sense and
 Avoid/ Due Regard Alternative Means of Compliance (SAA/DRAMOC) requirements. A-kit includes: Active Electronically Scanned Array (AESA) Radar, a sense and avoid processor, an upgraded Identification
 Friend or Foe (IFF) transponder, a Traffic Collision Avoidance System (TCAS) and associated wiring.

 [Detect And Avoid System (DAAS) (GCS) A-Kit] Includes a server and rack package in ground control station to enable full capability of DAAS on the aircraft.

 [Airborne Network Extension (ANE) / SkyTower ll (AV) A-Kit] Provides wiring and power distribution to the payload.

 [Airborne Network Extension (ANE) / SkyTower ll (GCS) A-Kit] Includes a server and rack package in ground control station to enable full capability of SkyTower II on the aircraft.

 [Electronic Warfare (EW) Sensor/ Cloud Surfer II (AV) A-Kit] Includes wiring and power distribution to the payload. Electronic Warfare (EW) A/B-kits procurements accounts for the three subsystems required to
 formulate an EW/ Cloud Surfer II kit. These subsystems consist of EW/ Cloud Surfer II Pod, Smart Sensor, and a Processing Exploitation and Dissemination (PED) workstation.

 [Electronic Warfare (EW)/ Cloud Surfer II Sensor (GCS) A-Kit] Provides a server and rack package in ground control station to enable full capability of EW/ Cloud Surfer II on the aircraft.

 [Electronic Warfare Sensor (Common Operating Picture (COP/GCS)) A-Kit] Provides a server and rack package in ground control station to disseminate the operational picture and the data from the aircraft's EW
 payload.


