1506N / 05 / 1                                                                        0507 / Marine Group 5 UAS Series                                                     1 / Marine Group 5 UAS Series (OSIP
                                                                                                                                                                           004-22)
ID Code (A=Service Ready, B=Not Service Ready) :                                                                           MDAP/MAIS Code:

 [Proliferated Low Earth Orbit (PLEO) (AV) A-Kit] Provides an antenna and wiring package to enable PLEO connectivity for aircraft command and control and data dissemination.

 [Proliferated Low Earth Orbit (PLEO) (GCS) A-Kit] Provides an antenna, server and rack package in ground control station to enable full capability of PLEO connectivity.

 [Smart Sensor (AV) A-Kit] Smart Sensor provides autonomy capability that controls Full Motion Video (FMV) and Synthetic Aperture Radar (SAR) sensors and fuses information, instantaneous transmission of
 FMV-SAR target tracks cued by EW pod. Smart Sensor is an EW enabling capability. The funding was broken out from EW to more accurately depict costs for each element.

 [Smart Sensor High Performance Computer (HPC)] High-Performance Computing (HPC) enables and enhances the capabilities of smart sensors. The HPC houses the AI software for on platform capabilities
 where it empowers smart sensors to move beyond simple data collection and transmission which allowing for crucial real-time decisions.

 [Electronic Warfare (EW) High TS/SCI and CDS A-Kit] Provides hardware, software, and algorithms, to enhance the EW Pod System with the ability to collect, process, store and transport higher than SECRET
 data. Includes enhancements to the pod, ground control element, and aircraft as well as the corresponding integration test and evaluation.

 [Automatic Identification System] Integrated Automatic Identification System (AIS) capability enhances maritime situational awareness.

 [Airborne Network Extension (ANE) / SkyTower ll B-Kit] Provides network extension across multiple waveforms to enable communication and data dissemination in the AOR.

 [Electronic Warfare (EW) Sensor B-Kit] Provides Electronic Surveillance to include geolocation, classification, emitter ID, and record capability. Electronic Warfare (EW) A/B-kits procurements accounts for the
 three subsystems required to formulate an EW kit. These subsystems consist of EW Pod, Smart Sensor, and a Processing Exploitation and Dissemination (PED) workstation.

 [Ground Control Station(GCS) Intel Com Directive(ICD)705 Compliant B-Kit] Provides for TS/SCI and above accreditation and upgrades of the common computing environment.

 [DuraNET B-Kit] DuraNET Provides dedicated Internet Protocol (IP) connection switching to ensure that mission critical data will be communicated efficiently between a variety of Unmanned Air Vehicle (UAV)
 platforms and the Warfighters on the ground.

 [Centerline Avionics Bay (CAB) B-Kit] Centerline Avionics Bay (CAB) GFE provides an externally mounted enclosure, wherein key additive platform components are integrated and operate in support of
 specialized Warfighter mission objectives. The CAB is a GFE component required for integration of capability enhancing payloads and sensors including DAAS and EW.

 [Identification Friend or Foe (IFF) (GFE)] Identification Friend or Foe (IFF) is an identification system designed for command and control. It sends a response to received interrogation signals that identifies specific
 information identifying it to the broadcaster. It enables military and civilian air traffic control interrogation systems to identify aircraft, vehicles or forces as friendly, as opposed to neutral or hostile, and to determine
 their bearing and range from the interrogator.

 [Radar Electronics Assembly (REA) (GFE)] The Radar Electronics Assembly (REA) is a small Space, Weight, and Power (SWaP) solution providing onboard edge computing for the Smart Sensor (SS) payload
 which includes Artificial Intelligence (AI), Automatic Target Recognition (ATR), and advanced mission processing. The REA software and hardware architecture facilitates the hosting of 3rd party algorithms
 required for SS operability.

 [B Kits/Non-Recurring] Non-recurring engineering (NRE) funds are required to correct deficiencies from initial testing and integrate full capability by ensuring the interoperability of the Airborne Network Extension
 (Sky Tower II), upgrading the Electronic Warfare (EW) system, integrating M-Code, and supporting the Detect and Avoid System (DAAS) integration. The NRE will also be utilized to address component
 obsolescence and enhance performance for the PLEO datalink through modernization.




