 Footnotes:
 (1)
     FY 2027 Unit cost increase is due to the negotiated tiered pricing structure that is currently on contract. FY 2027 is an option exercise of a previously negotiated contract option. FY 2027 budget request
 supports the continued acceleration of LBC procurement to improve reliability, readiness and address known threats to fill the capability gap until Next Generation Jammer Low Band (NGJ-LB) capability is
 fielded.
 (2)
       FY 2027 unit cost increases by 2% due to inflation and includes procurement of the patagium antennas to address specific threats.
 (3)
    FY 2027 procurement of Modernized Universal Exciter Upgrade (M-UEU) Phase 1 upgrade to address obsolescence issues and deliver additional capability. M-UEU is being upgraded in a multi-phase
 strategy to expedite delivery of capability to the Fleet.
 (4)
       FY 2027 Support equipment funding is required for modifications/additions to the ALQ-99 pod test to support LBC, addressing multiple obsolescence issues with existing ALQ-99 support equipment.



